d says, &#39;Beat your comrade!&#39; I take [it] and beat him. He says, &#39;that is not how one beats,&#39; takes that Nagan out of my hand, and gives me such a hard blow that I could not lift my hand any more. He says to me, &#39;That is how one beats Now will you know? Now beat your comrade.&#39; In such a...in such a way they tried to liquidate us in the quickest manner. And afterwards he took...and said..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "802.907","u": "What is a &#39;Nagan&#39;? [Nagan is the make of a revolver. He may confuse it with the term Nagaika, a short, heavy horse whip used by the cossacks]."},    {"who": "Kalman Eisenberg", "start": "804.719","u": "That is a rubber, a special...a special rubber...a thick one that with one blow..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "811.045","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Kalman Eisenberg", "start": "811.246","u": "One blow with it, then there shows...there is immediately a mark on that place, a black mark. There is immediately a black welt on that place."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "818.673","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Kalman Eisenberg", "start": "819.256","u": "That is a terrible thing which the Germans used a lot against the Jews."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "824.240","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Kalman Eisenberg", "start": "827.102","u": "And afterwards he took...he said for two people to fill up a RR-car with coal, and for two people to lay down on the floor and they should be entirely covered [buried]. After that, after they were covered..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "838.394","u": "Who said that that should be done?"},    {"who": "Kalman Eisenberg", "start": "839.860","u": "That...that...that Wehrmacht leader of the Germans, that Altoff."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "843.659","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Kalman Eisenberg", "start": "844.024","u": "He was a big leader of a factory. Altoff."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "848.224","u": "Hm, to cover them with coal?"},    {