the boards and cutting the wires. And a few people succeeded in escaping. At the same moment fire began falling from all four roofs, from the towers where the guards stood, and many, many were shot and a very small part escaped into the woods. But the majority of Jews were afraid to risk [it] and did not have the possibilities any more of running over to the fence and running away, because death awaited them immediately."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2438.495","u": "Where were you?"},    {"who": "Kalman Eisenberg", "start": "2439.685","u": "We...I myself was lying under a...under the barrack, under the block, not far from the wires and watched for the moment so that I could escape. But I noticed that terrible fire [shooting]. And the...and from that terrible fire I have noticed...and from...and the..and from the thrown grenades a lot of people were shattered and torn to pieces. Not a sign of them remained. Many people...the feet, the hands...and of one it even tore off the head. I noticed at the moment..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2474.085","u": "How was his head torn off? From the shooting or from..."},    {"who": "Kalman Eisenberg", "start": "2476.861","u": "From...from the grenades. From grenades."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2479.147","u": "Oh. Who was throwing grenades?"},    {"who": "Kalman Eisenberg", "start": "2480.625","u": "The...the...the guards. They saw..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2482.161","u": "And the guards were Ukrainians or..."},    {"who": "Kalman Eisenberg", "start": "2484.129","u": "The guards were Ukrainians and Germans."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2488.095","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Kalman Eisenberg", "start": "2488.874","u": "In a few seconds the whole lager was surrounded by many sentries and the Germans. And to escape was out of the question. Everybody [was] chased into the barrack. Everybody was silent, more dead than alive, and awaited the order when the moment is to arrive. Because